    <docBody>
        <dateline><date value="1920-12-03"/>and <place>Reading, Pa</place></dateline>
        <p>1914-deaths 302, under 1 year- 154 still born 154 38 2503 women 154</p>
        <p>Woman must be protected from incessant child bearing before she can actively participate
            in social life. She must triumph over natures laws which have kept her in bondage.</p>
        <p>She must triumph over these as man has in electricity ship building etc. She must
            challenge these laws which have made her a child bearing machine. Only then can she
            develop her personality &amp; individuality &amp; prepare with man for that greatest of
            all goals, the emanciaption of the human race.</p>
        <p>Reading, Pa <del><person reg="Steveson, Robert Louis">Robert Louis
                Stevenson</person></del>
            <del>Condemnation is misunderstanding</del></p>
        <p><person reg="Wells, H.G.">H.G.</person> intelligence slow to develop</p>
        <p>Definition of birth Control</p>
        <p>Nature</p>
        <p>Two kinds of people Large &amp; small families&rcub; Poverty disease misery overcrowding
            unemployment child labor infant mortality</p>
        <p>Two <del>kinds of</del> women start alike&rcub;prudery on sex subject&rcub; inventions
            discoveries vegetable &amp; animal kingdom </p>
        <p>Legislative palliatives &amp; &lcub;charities not fundamental 8 hour day-for
            mothers&rcub; 7 million child laborers 300,000 children under 1 year die 23,000 mothers
            die a year 25,0000 illegal abortions feeble minded &amp; prostitution</p>
        <p>T.B. 7-4-heart disease-kidney disease </p>
        <p>Insane &amp; <emph rend="underline">T.B</emph> syphilitic women care </p>
        <p>Abortions--my last case--quacks</p>
        <p><place>England</place>-<place reg="Netherlands"
                >Holland</place>-<place>Germany</place>-<place>Russia</place> (new movement) clinics
            young people marry</p>
        <p><place reg="United States">U.S.A.</place> laws-none in <place reg="Pennslyvania"
                >Pa</place>-Peace Treaty</p>
        <p>Clinics-keynote of woman social awakening</p>
